Press cookie dough onto an ungreased 12-in. pizza pan. Bake at 350 degrees F for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth; stir in yogurt. Spread over crust to within 1/2 in. of edges. Sprinkle with blueberries. Cut into wedges. Refrigerate leftovers.